Findings: The most purchased was the TM195 being bought by 45% of the customers. The TM498 was the second most purchased. The TM798 was third. Around 58% of the treadmills being purchased were done so by males. More Partnerend people purchased then signles. The average use by males if more than females. Younger people are buying more trendmills. People making under 70k are buying more treadmills. The majority of people buying treadmills have a college education.

Customer Profiles: TM195: Mainly male. Make under 55k. Mostly in the mid 20s for age. Most have a Bachlores degree. Fitness levels are average. The usage is at 3 to 4 times a week.

TM498: Mainly Males althoug single females bought this model more than single males. Make under 50k. Mostly in mid 20s for age. Most have a Bachlores degree. Fitness level is average. The usage is at 3 to 4 times a week.

TM798: Mainly Males. Make over 70k. Mostly upper 20s. Most have advanced degrees. Most usage between 4 to 5 days.

Recommendation: The TM195 and the TM 498 should be markketed as an entery level treadmill. The TM798 should be marketed as the high end treadmill The TM798 should be marketed for athletes and hard core workout people. To add more female customers we should hold commercials that show off more females using the product. To add more customer above the age of 35 we should add inmore representation of that age group.
